        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is fastest to launch?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Durable wins by miles. 30 seconds consistently. The plumber's site went live in 12 minutes total‚Äîfrom zero to published. 10Web is fast (5 minutes) but requires more customization. Webflow has no AI generation‚Äîbuilding from scratch takes hours to days."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is most expensive?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow is most expensive: $18-212/month. CMS features start at $29, ecommerce at $42 minimum. 10Web is best value: $10-60/month including managed hosting. Durable: $15-100/month. For the design agency, Webflow's $45/month was worth it‚Äîdesign quality drove $42,000 in revenue. But for simple sites, Webflow is overpriced."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which has the steepest learning curve?",
